The Chronicle Whinsley Masara/Sharon Buwerimwe,Â Chronicle Reporters A Zimbabwe Prisons and Correctional Services officer stationed at Khami Maximum Prison in Bulawayo is battling for life in hospital after he shot himself in an attempted suicide. Ngonidzashe Mutoti (36) who is admitted to Mpilo Central Hospital shot himself once in the chest while he was on duty at the prison. The incident occurred at around 1PM on Wednesday.